  "text": "The E0505 error 'cannot move out of X because it is borrowed' is generated through a multi-stage process in the Rust compiler's borrow checker.\n\n**Detection Stage (lib.rs):**\nThe borrow checker's main entry point is the `mir_borrowck` function in `compiler/rustc_borrowck/src/lib.rs`. This function creates a `BorrowCheckRootCtxt` and calls `do_mir_borrowck()` to analyze the MIR. Within this context, a `MirBorrowckCtxt` instance implements the borrow checker logic using a `ResultsVisitor` pattern that walks the MIR.\n\nDuring dataflow analysis, the `check_access_for_conflict` function (line 1246 in lib.rs) is the core conflict detection mechanism. This function iterates through all active borrows using `each_borrow_involving_path` and checks if an access (read, write, or move) conflicts with any borrow. When a `WriteKind::Move` operation is encountered on a place that has an active borrow, the code matches this pattern (line 1361-1362) and identifies a conflict.\n\n**Place Conflict Checking (places_conflict.rs):**\nThe `places_conflict` function in `compiler/rustc_borrowck/src/places_conflict.rs` provides utility functions for determining whether borrowing/access places overlap. The underlying `borrow_conflicts_with_place` function handles the detailed logic of comparing place projections to determine disjointness.\n\n**Error Reporting (conflict_errors.rs):**\nOnce a move-while-borrowed conflict is detected, the code calls `report_move_out_while_borrowed` (line 1533 in `compiler/rustc_borrowck/src/diagnostics/conflict_errors.rs`). This function constructs a detailed diagnostic by:\n- Describing the place being moved and the borrowed place\n- Retrieving span information for both the move and the borrow\n- Calling `cannot_move_when_borrowed` to create the error\n\n**Error Creation (borrowck_errors.rs):**\nThe `cannot_move_when_borrowed` function (line 16 in `compiler/rustc_borrowck/src/borrowck_errors.rs`) creates the diagnostic error by instantiating a `MoveBorrow` struct with the relevant information.\n\n**Diagnostic Definition (session_diagnostics.rs):**\nThe `MoveBorrow` struct (in `compiler/rustc_borrowck/src/session_diagnostics.rs`) is decorated with the `#[diag(borrowck_cannot_move_when_borrowed, code = E0505)]` attribute, which associates this error with error code E0505.\n\n**Error Documentation (E0505.md):**\nThe file `compiler/rustc_error_codes/src/error_codes/E0505.md` provides user-friendly explanation and examples of when this error occurs and how to fix it."
}

